-- Jelasic to Advise Serbia’s Finance Minister on Banks, Blic Says
-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 2012-10-01T08:16:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-01/jelasic-to-advise-serbia-s-finance-minister-on-banks-blic-says.html
Radovan Jelasic, the head of  Erste
Group Bank AG (EBS) ’s Hungarian unit and Serbia’s former central bank
chief, will advise the Serbian government on the banking
industry,  Blic  newspaper reported, citing the finance minister.  Jelasic will keep his position at Erste while making
monthly trips to Belgrade and will be in “constant
communication” with Serbian authorities, the report quoted
Finance Minister  Mladjan Dinkic  as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  